see below more info:PART 1: PRD Addendum - AI Sovereignty & BYOK
This section updates the "User Stories" and "Tech Stack" to explicitly support user-defined AI backends.
2.1 Updated User Stories (AI Section)
As a privacy-focused developer, I want to connect my local Ollama instance, so that I can use AI summarization and text generation without my data ever leaving my machine.
Acceptance Criteria:
Settings menu has an "AI Provider" section.
Option to select "Local (Ollama)" and input a host URL (default: http://localhost:11434).
Dropdown to fetch and select available models (e.g., llama3, mistral).
System works fully offline if the model is local.
As a power user, I want to bring my own OpenAI/Anthropic API Key, so that I am billed directly and get higher rate limits than the free tier might offer.
Acceptance Criteria:
Input fields for API Keys (stored securely in local storage/Keychain).
Toggle between "Cloud Provider" and "Local Provider".
3.1 Updated Tech Stack (AI Layer)
AI Abstraction Layer: Vercel AI SDK (Core) or LangChain.js for uniform streaming interfaces across providers.
Local Inference: Direct HTTP connectors to Ollama API.
Security:
Web: Keys stored in localStorage (encrypted via user password if possible).
Electron: Keys stored via Electron SafeStorage API.
PART 2: Step-by-Step Build (The Implementation)
This guide focuses on setting up the AI Infrastructure within the existing Monorepo structure defined in the PRD.
